  <prompt>
    Create `Services/Compose/ComposeSessionService.cs` â€” the thin binding layer that ties a Compose editor session to the existing `ChatSession` model via `DocumentId`. For ephemeral docs (Path B), `DocumentId` is the SPE drive-item id; after first-Save promotion (FR-06), `DocumentId` is updated to the `sprk_documentid`. This service consumes the existing `ChatSessionManager` + `SessionPersistenceService` infrastructure â€” it does NOT create a new session entity or duplicate the Redis/Cosmos/Dataverse three-tier pipeline.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior .NET developer who understands the Spaarke ChatSession three-tier persistence (Redis hot â†’ Cosmos warm â†’ Dataverse cold) and ADR-015 multi-tenant isolation. Comfortable building thin faĂ§ades over existing infrastructure.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `Services/Compose/ComposeSessionService.cs` + `IComposeSessionService` interface exist. The service binds a Compose editor session to an existing `ChatSession` via `DocumentId`, and exposes idempotent `RebindToDocumentIdAsync` to handle the ephemeralâ†’promoted transition after first-Save (FR-07).
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-07 requires Compose to use the existing `ChatSession` model with `DocumentId` binding â€” NOT a new session entity. The session must persist across browser refresh via the existing three-tier infrastructure unchanged. This service is the thin seam that gives Compose a stable API while reusing all the heavy-lifting (compaction at 15 messages, archive at 50, multi-tenant Tier 3 isolation).
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
