  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-013">No AI-internal types injected (`IOpenAiClient`, `IPlaybookService`). Consuming the existing `ChatSessionManager` is fine â€” it is not an AI client, it is the session-store facade.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-015">Multi-tenant isolation Tier 3 â€” inherited via the underlying `ChatSession` infrastructure. Do NOT bypass the existing tenant-scope filters.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">MUST reuse existing `ChatSession` model + `ChatSessionManager` + `SessionPersistenceService`. MUST NOT introduce a new session entity, new Redis key shape, or new Cosmos partition.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">`RebindToDocumentIdAsync` is idempotent â€” multiple calls with the same new `DocumentId` are a no-op after the first.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">MUST NOT extend `sprk_analysis.sprk_chathistory` (superseded; see CLAUDE.md Supersession Map).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <justification>
    <existing>`src/server/api/Sprk.Bff.Api/Services/Ai/Chat/ChatSessionManager.cs:42` (the canonical session-binding service; consumed via existing three-tier facade) and `Services/Ai/Sessions/SessionPersistenceService.cs` (the three-tier persistence layer).</existing>
    <extension>No â€” extending `ChatSessionManager` directly would conflate conversation-memory concerns with editor-host session binding semantics (ephemeralâ†’promoted DocumentId transition). A thin `ComposeSessionService` consumes ChatSessionManager without modifying its surface; this is exactly the seam the spec FR-07 calls for.</extension>
    <cost-of-doing-nothing>FR-07 fails â€” Compose has no place to perform the ephemeralâ†’promoted DocumentId rebind (FR-06 idempotency depends on this), and endpoints (task 024) have no session API to call.</cost-of-doing-nothing>
  </justification>

